<h2>About</h2>
<p>As a vetern software engineer and technology enusist, Nick understands the importance that technology plays with in an organization and the substantial impact it can have when combined with marketing and design.</p>
<h2>Background</h2>
<p>Nick graduated from Penn State with a degree is Information Science and Technology (IST).  After he graduated he landed his first job with the prestigious Lockheed Martin in King of Prussia, PA.  While at Lockheed Martin, he learned the importance that process plays in acheiving goals in a timely manner.  Most of the software development work Nick did was based around the ISO 9001 Level 5 engineering process, which only a handful of companies in the world have acheived.  After working for Lockheed Martin, Nick continued his career at LA Weight Loss, in Horsham, PA, and lead the software development effort of creating a multi-lingual distributed point of sale system that handled over 650 million dollars annually.  The point of sale system, SlimPOS, his team of 8 created, helped improve the reporting and monitization of profits in a more organized way to the owner of the company and the individual franchises.</p>
<p>Nick then went on to found Managed Fusion. He felt his company could really help business owners bring all their marketing, technology, and design needs together in a synergy that reduce costs, improve customer relations, and gained technological advatages over their compeditors.</p>
